verbose_text: It might be possible that over-expression of Exportin-5 stabilized the pre-miRNA forms to such degree that it prevents further processing and therefore lead to a decrease in the mature levels XREF_BIBR; (iii) Exportin-5 levels in the cells are saturated; (iv) an excess of Exportin-5 could associate with other factors which lead to their exclusion from the nucleus and to reduced miRNA biogenesis activity.
